mocha.addFile.description: Adds file to be loaded for execution.

mocha.allowUncaught.description: Enables or disables uncaught errors to propagate.

mocha.asyncOnly.description: Forces all tests to either accept a done callback or return a promise.

mocha.bail.description: Enables or disables bailing on the first failure.

mocha.checkLeaks.description: Enables or disables checking for global variables leaked while running tests.

mocha.color.description: Enables or disables TTY color output by screen-oriented reporters.

mocha.diff.description: Enables or disables reporter to include diff in test failure output.

mocha.dispose.description: Manually dispose this mocha instance. Mark this instance as disposed and unable to run more tests.

mocha.enableGlobalSetup.description: Toggle execution of any global setup fixture(s)

mocha.enableGlobalTeardown.description: Toggle execution of any global teardown fixture(s)

mocha.fgrep.description: Sets grep filter after escaping RegExp special characters.

mocha.forbidOnly.description: Causes tests marked only to fail the suite.

mocha.forbidPending.description: Causes pending tests and tests marked skip to fail the suite.

mocha.fullTrace.description: Displays full stack trace upon test failure.

mocha.global.description: Specifies whitelist of variable names to be expected in global scope.

mocha.globalSetup.description: Configures one or more global setup fixtures. If given no parameters, unsets any previously-set fixtures.

mocha.globalTeardown.description: Configures one or more global teardown fixtures. If given no parameters, unsets any previously-set fixtures.

mocha.grep.description: Sets grep filter used to select specific tests for execution.

mocha.growl.description: Enables desktop notification support if prerequisite software installed.

mocha.hasGlobalSetupFixtures.description: Returns true if one or more global setup fixtures have been supplied.

mocha.hasGlobalTeardownFixtures.description: Returns true if one or more global teardown fixtures have been supplied.

mocha.inlineDiffs.description: Enables or disables reporter to use inline diffs (rather than +/-) in test failure output.

mocha.lazyLoadFiles.description: Disables implicit call to Mocha#loadFiles in Mocha#run. This setting is used by watch mode, parallel mode, and for loading ESM files.

mocha.loadFilesAsync.description: The implementation relies on Node's require and import to execute the test interface functions and will be subject to its cache. Supports both CJS and ESM modules.

mocha.reporter.description: Sets reporter to reporter, defaults to 'spec'.

mocha.retries.description: Sets the number of times to retry failed tests.

mocha.rootHooks.description: Assigns hooks to the root suite.

mocha.run.description: To run tests multiple times (or to run tests in files that are already in the require cache), make sure to clear them from the cache first!

mocha.runGlobalSetup.description: Run any global setup fixtures sequentially, if any. This is automatically called by Mocha#run unless the runGlobalSetup option is false. The context object this function resolves with should be consumed by Mocha#runGlobalTeardown.

mocha.runGlobalTeardown.description: Run any global teardown fixtures sequentially, if any. This is automatically called by Mocha#run unless the runGlobalTeardown option is false. Should be called with context object returned by Mocha#runGlobalSetup, if applicable.

mocha.ui.description: Sets test UI name, defaults to 'bdd'.

mocha.unloadFiles.description: This allows required files to be 'freshly' reloaded, providing the ability to reuse a Mocha instance programmatically. Note: does not clear ESM module files from the cache.

assert.fail.description: Throw a failure. Node.js assert module-compatible.

assert.equal.description: Asserts non-strict equality (==) of actual and expected.

assert.notEqual.description: Asserts non-strict inequality (!=) of actual and expected.
